```typescript
minPrice: typeof minPrice === "string" && !isNaN(parseFloat(minPrice)) ? parseFloat(minPrice) : undefined
```

Remove import of `products` from `../data.js`; add import of service functions from `../services/product-service.js`.

### Step 5: Refactor `src/routes/orders.ts`

Same pattern — thin HTTP adapters calling service functions:

```typescript
router.get("/orders", (req, res) => {
  const result = listOrders({ userId: /* parsed */, status: /* parsed */ });
  res.json(result);
});

router.get("/orders/:id", (req, res) => {
  const result = getOrder(parseInt(req.params.id, 10));
  if (!result.success) { res.status(result.status).json({ error: result.error }); return; }
  res.json(result.data);
});

router.post("/orders", (req, res) => {
  const result = createOrder(req.body as CreateOrderInput);
  if (!result.success) { res.status(result.status).json({ error: result.error }); return; }
  res.status(201).json(result.data);
});

router.patch("/orders/:id/status", (req, res) => {
  const { status } = req.body as { status: string };
  const result = updateOrderStatus(parseInt(req.params.id, 10), status);
  if (!result.success) { res.status(result.status).json({ error: result.error }); return; }
  res.json(result.data);
});
```

**userId parsing edge case**: Must check `!isNaN(parseInt(userId, 10))` before passing to service.

Remove imports of `orders`, `products`, `getNextOrderId` from `../data.js`; add import of service functions from `../services/order-service.js`.

### Step 6: Verify

Run `npx tsc --noEmit` (type-check) and `npm test` (all 12 existing tests must pass).

## Files Changed

| File | Action |
|---|---|
| `src/types.ts` | Modify — add service result types |
| `src/services/product-service.ts` | **Create** — 3 functions |
| `src/services/order-service.ts` | **Create** — 4 functions |
| `src/routes/products.ts` | Modify — replace inline logic with service calls |
| `src/routes/orders.ts` | Modify — replace inline logic with service calls |
| `src/app.ts` | No change |
| `src/data.ts` | No change |
| `tests/*.test.ts` | No change |

## Pitfalls

- **Error message strings must be character-identical** to current route responses (e.g. backtick templates like `` `Cannot transition from ${order.status} to ${status}` ``)
- **ESM import extensions**: All imports must use `.js` extensions (Node16 module resolution)
- **`src/services/` directory** does not exist yet — must be created
- **Stock deduction ordering** in `createOrder` must match current interleaved pattern

## Verification

```bash
npx tsc --noEmit   # TypeScript strict mode type-check
npm test            # All 12 tests (5 product + 7 order) must pass
```

